Description: Fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The rear is convex with the impression of leather, probably from a leather bag. In the break the impression of a turned cord with a width of 0.3cm is visible. The upper side is flat with the lateral sides bending downwards on one side and upwards on another side, and showing several finger imprints. about half of the impression of an oval scarab-like seal is visible. Recognisable is a wAs-sceptre on the left, in the centre an oval ring with a spiral inside in the shape of a sideways lying S. Underneath a nwb-sign. Same motif as on EA86905.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
